HELP VIEWER
===========
- Alt+y / Ctrl+a y open this file in less.
- Press / to search, n/N for next/previous match, q to quit.

TMUX / PSMUX HYBRID KEYBINDS
===========================

This cheatsheet shows both:
- the hybrid no-prefix binds we added to feel closer to zellij
- the important tmux/psmux defaults you are still inheriting behind Prefix

Friendly help
-------------
Alt+y                    Open this cheatsheet
Ctrl+a y                 Open this cheatsheet
Ctrl+a Y                 Show raw tmux/psmux key table
Ctrl+a ?                 Show raw tmux/psmux key table

No-prefix binds (zellij-style layer)
------------------------------------
Focus panes
Alt+h/j/k/l              Focus pane left/down/up/right
Alt+Left/Down/Up/Right   Focus pane left/down/up/right

Pane management
Alt+n                    Smart split on the longest axis
Alt+d                    Split below
Alt+e                    Split right
Alt+x                    Close pane
Alt+z                    Toggle pane zoom
Alt+f                    Popup shell

Windows
Alt+, / Alt+.            Previous / next window
Alt+1..9                 Go to window 1..9 when the host terminal passes them
Alt+F1..F9               Fallback window 1..9 for hosts that steal Alt+1..9

Layouts / help
Alt+[ / Alt+]            Previous / next layout
Alt+s                    Enter copy mode
Alt+w                    Chooser
Alt+y                    Open this cheatsheet

Prefix basics (Ctrl+a)
----------------------
Ctrl+a Ctrl+a            Send Ctrl+a to the program inside the pane
Ctrl+a :                 Command prompt
Ctrl+a ?                 Raw key table
Ctrl+a y                 Friendly cheatsheet
Ctrl+a Y                 Raw key table

Windows behind prefix
---------------------
Ctrl+a c                 New window (canonical tmux)
Ctrl+a t                 New window (zellij-style alias)
Ctrl+a n                 Next window
Ctrl+a p                 Previous window
Ctrl+a w                 Window chooser
Ctrl+a g                 Chooser alias
Ctrl+a 0..9              Go to window 0..9
Ctrl+a ,                 Rename window (canonical tmux)
Ctrl+a r                 Rename window (alias)
Ctrl+a &                 Kill current window
Ctrl+a i / o             Move window left / right
Ctrl+a Space             Next layout
Ctrl+a Alt+1             Layout: even-horizontal
Ctrl+a Alt+2             Layout: even-vertical
Ctrl+a Alt+3             Layout: main-horizontal
Ctrl+a Alt+4             Layout: main-vertical
Ctrl+a Alt+5             Layout: tiled

Session / client behind prefix
------------------------------
Ctrl+a d                 Detach client
Ctrl+a s                 Session chooser
Ctrl+a (                 Previous session
Ctrl+a )                 Next session
Ctrl+a $                 Rename session
Ctrl+a Ctrl+q            Kill current psmux session (with confirmation)

Panes behind prefix
-------------------
Focus / selection
Ctrl+a h/j/k/l           Focus pane left/down/up/right
Ctrl+a Left/Down/Up/Right
                         Focus pane left/down/up/right
Ctrl+a o                 Select next pane
Ctrl+a ;                 Jump to previously active pane
Ctrl+a q                 Show pane numbers

Pane management
Ctrl+a "                 Split below
Ctrl+a %                 Split right
Ctrl+a x                 Close pane
Ctrl+a z                 Toggle pane zoom
Ctrl+a { / }             Move pane backward / forward
Ctrl+a !                 Break pane into its own window
Ctrl+a f                 Popup shell
Ctrl+a m                 Show pane/window move hint

Resize behind prefix
--------------------
Ctrl+a H/J/K/L           Resize left/down/up/right by 5
Ctrl+a Shift+Left/Down/Up/Right
                         Resize left/down/up/right by 5
Ctrl+a Alt+Left/Down/Up/Right
                         Inherited tmux resize by 5
Ctrl+a Ctrl+Left/Down/Up/Right
                         Inherited tmux fine resize by 1

Copy / paste / buffers
----------------------
Ctrl+a [                 Enter copy mode
Ctrl+a ]                 Paste latest buffer
Ctrl+a =                 Choose buffer interactively
Ctrl+a #                 List buffers

Copy mode (vi)
--------------
Movement
h j k l                  Left / down / up / right
w b e                    Word motions
0 ^ $                    Start / first nonblank / end of line
g / G                    Top / bottom of scrollback
Ctrl+u / Ctrl+d          Half page up / down
Ctrl+b / Ctrl+f          Full page up / down
PageUp / PageDown        Full page up / down

Search
/                        Search forward
?                        Search backward
n / N                    Next / previous match

Selection / copy
Space                    Start selection
v / Ctrl+v               Toggle rectangle selection
V                        Line selection
y / Enter                Copy and exit
o                        Swap cursor/anchor ends
Esc / q                  Exit copy mode

Notes
-----
- Prefix is Ctrl+a.
- The hybrid layer is intentionally incomplete: tmux defaults remain available behind Prefix.
- Some Alt combinations can be intercepted by WezTerm or Windows Terminal.
  If Alt+1..9 does not work, use Alt+F1..F9 or Ctrl+a 1..9.
- psmux currently folds Alt+Shift+letter onto Alt+letter in your setup.
  For resize, use Prefix+H/J/K/L or Prefix+Shift+Arrow.
